‎جُمْعَة مُباركة Jum3a Mubaraka Instafam 😊 Feeling super blessed this Friday for having been able to spend this past Thanksgiving 🦃 with my entire El-Yacoubi clan in Northern Virginia for the first time in a decade 😱 It’s a rare occasion when all 8 siblings + our kids come together so when it happens, magic happens 🪄 These are the people that I’ve known since the 80’s and they have a way of filling my cup with so much meaning, light and love 🕊️ 

Truthfully the trip was transformational. It reminded us all of just how fast time is passing and the importance of being intentional about getting together, and staying together 💞 Hearts were so full while memories were made for a lifetime. Praying our hearts always incline toward each other and always remain in alignment with one another🤲 ameeeeen 🫶

May your Friday + families be blessed in every way 🙏🏻💖

#Mashallah #Alhamdulelah #familyovereverything #deenanddunya #thanksgiving #fifaworldcup #thankgivingbreak #virginia #eastcoast #winnergy

12.18.22 💓 Gained a new sister this past weekend celebrating my awesome BIL @bchaby marriage to his beautiful bride @sarahnajjj 🥰 May Allah protect and preserve their union and bless it endlessly & always 🤲 drop an AMEEN for the lovely couple👇🙏🏻🫶🧿#mashallah #alhamdulelah #muslimmarriage

🎓 This past Friday May 5th, marked a monumental day in my life the day I passed my doctoral defense in Religious Studies from UC Riverside 🥲 a day I have loooong awaited for and have been working toward for 8 years. I couldn’t be happier and more grateful for the outpour of love, support, and especially dua that I FULLY felt from so many of you 🥹

As you can imagine, I was nervous the week leading up to my defense so I decided not to share with everyone that it was a public defense via zoom and instead wanted it to be a private affair but I swear I could feel the love and duas people were making for me and it really lifted me and my spirits in the best ways which made me excited for people to tune into so I posted about it 24 hours before it was game time and I couldn’t be happier with that decision. It was truly special seeing so many of my friends family and community members while I was defending and to have you all witness this moment with me is something I will cherish forever 🫶

THANK YOU ALL from the depths of my heart for your love and support. I have read every single message, text, DM and will do my best to respond. Beyond blessed allahuma laka alhamd 🤲 May Allah continue to shower us all with endless blessings, health, prosperity, and piety and make us of the winners in this life and the next 🙏🏻💖🎓#PHinisheD #PHreeDom #Alhamdulelah #Classof2023 #Graduationhereicome #Mashallah #PhD #ReligiousStudies #ucriverside

In a time where we are all incomprehensibly devastated from watching the carnage that is happening in P@lestin3 right now I’m trying to take my feelings of hopelessness and harness it through memory by ensuring that we not only remember this moment but also the beautiful historical land + people of our precious P@lestin€. 

Memory is a powerful form of resistance during times of conflict and calamities. We can keep the memory of P@lestin3  alive and well in our homes by teaching our children about its geographic location on the map, its historical significance in Islam, the sacred Masjid Al-Aqsa, the rich culture + cuisine, and the list goes on.

In keeping the memory of Pal€stin$ alive, I’ve partnered up with @Dhad.USA to raise funds for P@l3stinian humanitarian aid. They produced this beautiful map of Palestine that is a great activity for your kids and a powerful visual in our homes. I will personally match every purchase of this map as donations directly to the cause. Every dollar counts. Link in posted in my story 🔗 🗺️

📣 Salam 2024! I’m starting off this new year with renewed intention, purpose, vision and a VERY special announcement that I’ve been working toward for a while now. I embarked on the homeschooling journey 🏡 this past year and my heart has found a resting place throughout this process. Being the central influence in my children’s educational and moral formation puts my heart at ease and has brought me into alignment with one of my greatest purposes in life which is Arabic and Islamic learning.

📣Homeschooling has allowed me to take a deep dive into teaching my kids Arabic and Islamic Studies which is the driving force behind my new venture: 
🌟– ALIGNMENT ACADEMY – 🌟
a children’s Arabic & Islamic Studies program for kids ages 4-7. It’s a private home-based program where I will be teaching Arabic language instruction through Classical and Modern Standard Arabic. It includes experiential learning, phonetic, semantic, and syntactic learning through Quranic contexts, concepts and verses. 

📣This program also offers an Islamic Studies section covering foundational Islamic principles, prophetic stories and characteristics, adab, anasheed, and attributes of The Divine, Islamic history with a special segment on the significance of Palestine in Islam 🇵🇸, exclusive Ramadan program, and Quranic memorization. I am so excited to invite the children of our communities to join this program for a very unique Islamic learning experience. 

📣The inspiration behind this project is my beloved father: Sheikh Dr. Hassan El-Yacoubi, a P@lestinian refugee who dedicated his life ensuring not one or two or three but all EIGHT of his children learned the language of the Quran so it could serve as the guiding light in our lives beyond his lifetime. Through his diligence and God’s grace, his dream came true. I love you baba, this one’s for you! 🥹🥹🥹🫶✊🤲

🔗 Link in bio to register your kids for the Spring semester! Follow @alignment_Academy2024 for more info and our recs on all things Arabic & Islamic learning 🌟

Tonight was truly one of the most special nights. I was a walking 🍉 and enjoyed every second standing in solidarity with my community and the right side of history. A night of healing and helping our hearts carve a viable path forward as American Muslims during these dark times. Was a real treat sharing the stage with @brothercornelwest @dr.soboh @lsarsour and Malcolm X — one of my mentors AND birthday twins😊

We discussed how the political climate has shifted over the past three months, the project of liberation, how to run with the moment of mass mobilization within the Muslim community, how to invest in Muslim entrepreneurial enterprises, and how to hold power without comprising our value systems. 

Thanks to the incredible efforts of @muslimvisionariesglobal who are what their name states: Muslim Visionaries 👏 and @knafehqueens for injecting life, energy, and purpose into all of our lives. #liberation #islaminamerica #cornelwest2024 #gametime #organize #muslimpower #powerandpolitics
